WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.161
Prognosis depends heavily on etiology and initial

00:00:03.161 --> 00:00:04.064
hemodynamic presentation.

00:00:04.064 --> 00:00:07.225
Lymphocytic myocarditis carries the most favorable prognosis

00:00:07.225 --> 00:00:10.386
— 50 to 60 percent achieve full

00:00:10.386 --> 00:00:11.289
myocardial recovery.

00:00:11.289 --> 00:00:14.451
Giant cell myocarditis has the worst outcomes,

00:00:14.451 --> 00:00:17.612
with median survival under 6 months without

00:00:17.612 --> 00:00:18.063
transplantation.

00:00:18.063 --> 00:00:21.224
Key clinical takeaways: maintain a high index

00:00:21.224 --> 00:00:24.385
of suspicion in young patients with chest

00:00:24.385 --> 00:00:27.546
pain and new ECG changes; CMR is

00:00:27.546 --> 00:00:30.707
the non-invasive diagnostic standard; fulminant presentations require

00:00:30.707 --> 00:00:33.868
immediate MCS — do not delay; and

00:00:33.868 --> 00:00:37.029
activity restriction is mandatory during the inflammatory

00:00:37.029 --> 00:00:37.481
phase.

00:00:37.481 --> 00:00:40.642
Early recognition and guideline-directed therapy are essential

00:00:40.642 --> 00:00:42.900
to preventing irreversible myocardial damage.
